      • getProperty

        public static String getProperty(String xmlFileName,
                                 String key,
                                 String defaultValue,
                                 String categoryName)
        Deprecated. 
        This is the real implementation. It will return the value of the property for a given XML file. First of all, it checks if the name of the category exists. If not, then it will use the name of the default category. The next step is that it will look for the property. If it is not found in the category, it will look inside the default category (inheritance). If it still cannot find the property, it will return the defaultValue.
        Parameters:
        xmlFileName - - name of the XML configuration file
        key - - name of the property to searcfor
        defaultValue - - the defaultValue that will be returned if the property cannot be found
        categoryName - - the name of the category
        Returns:
        String
